description: Deletes an Amazon EKS add-on. When you remove an add-on, it's deleted from the cluster. You can always manually start an add-on on the cluster using the Kubernetes API.

parameters.name: addonName
parameters.description: The name of the add-on. The name must match one of the names returned by ListAddons.

nested_items.name: addonName
nested_items.description: The name of the add-on.

nested_items.name: clusterName
nested_items.description: The name of your cluster.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the add-on.

nested_items.name: addonVersion
nested_items.description: The version of the add-on.

nested_items.name: issues
nested_items.description: An object representing the health issues for an add-on.

nested_items.name: code
nested_items.description: A code that describes the type of issue.

nested_items.name: message
nested_items.description: A message that provides details about the issue and what might cause it.

nested_items.name: resourceIds
nested_items.description: The resource IDs of the issue.
(string) ---

nested_items.name: addonArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the add-on.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The Unix epoch timestamp at object creation.

nested_items.name: modifiedAt
nested_items.description: The Unix epoch timestamp for the last modification to the object.

nested_items.name: serviceAccountRoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the IAM role that's bound to the Kubernetes ServiceAccount object that the add-on uses.
(string) ---
(string) ---

nested_items.name: publisher
nested_items.description: The publisher of the add-on.

nested_items.name: owner
nested_items.description: The owner of the add-on.

nested_items.name: marketplaceInformation
nested_items.description: Information about an Amazon EKS add-on from the Amazon Web Services Marketplace.

nested_items.name: productId
nested_items.description: The product ID from the Amazon Web Services Marketplace.

nested_items.name: productUrl
nested_items.description: The product URL from the Amazon Web Services Marketplace.

nested_items.name: configurationValues
nested_items.description: The configuration values that you provided.

nested_items.name: podIdentityAssociations
nested_items.description: An array of Pod Identity Assocations owned by the Addon. Each EKS Pod Identity association maps a role to a service account in a namespace in the cluster.
(string) ---
